<plot>An unhappy couple (Alice Brady, Lionel Barrymore) watch as their daughter (Mary Carlisle) throws herself at an older man (Conway Tearle) because he is a sophisticated artist. The daughter doesn't know that her aunt (Katherine Alexander) is the man's lover. At a weekend retreat, everything comes to a head when the mother (Brady) plans to run off with the artist while a young man (William Janney) pursues the daughter.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?494588</url></doc>
